[[File:Yi San-hae.jpg|thumbnail|Yi Sanhae]] {{Infobox Korean name| hangul=이산해| hanja=李山海| rr=Yi Sanhae| mr=Yi Sanhae| }} {{Korean name|[[Lee (Korean name)|Yi]]}}
'''Yi Sanhae''' ([[korea]]n:이산해, 李山海, 1539 ~ 1609, was Korean politician, scholar, and writer of the [[Joseon]] period. He served as [[Yeonguijeong|Chief State Councilor]] from 1590-1592 and 1600-1602. Yi was a member of the political faction the [[Easterners (Korean political faction)|Easterners]] and when this split into the Northerners and Southerners, Yi became leader of the [[Northerners (Korean political faction)|Northerners]] faction. [[Courtesy name]] was Yeosu(여수), nickname was Agye(아계, 鵝溪)·Jongnamsuong(종남수옹, 終南睡翁))·Jukpiong(죽피옹, 竹皮翁)·Sichongeosa(시촌거사, 枾村居士).
== Book == * 《Agye jip》(아계집, 鵝溪集) * 《Agye yugo》(아계유고, 鵝溪遺稿)
== Popular culture == * Portrayed by [[Ahn Suk-hwan]] in the 2014 [[KBS2]] TV series ''[[The King's Face]]''.
